The Vice President of the United States, Kamala Harris, spoke at the Sofitel Mexico City Reforma in Mexico City. She emphasized the administration's support for workers and unions, stating that they believe unions help build the middle class and are important for workers' rights. She also mentioned that she met with the President of Mexico, who shares the same sentiment. Harris expressed the United States' commitment to supporting organized labor and announced an additional $130 million investment in Mexico for technical assistance and cooperation over the next four years. This assistance will be directed towards implementing labor reform, strengthening labor standards, protecting workers, promoting acceptable working conditions, and addressing child labor. Harris highlighted the importance of collective bargaining and the need for workers to have equal footing in negotiations with employers to ensure fair outcomes.